testSteps.description: 1: Anna checking her borrowing power by using online ANZ homeloan calculator ({testCase=Testcase HL-1 : User entering valid data, expectedmessage=$482,000, appType=Single, dependents=0, propertyType=Home, income=80000, otherIncome=10000, livingExpenses=500, loanRepayments=0, otherloanRepayments=100, otherCommitments=0, totalCClimit=10000})

children.description: Given Anna visits anz homeloan calculator webpage
User navigating to ANZ home loan calculator webpage

When Anna entering details on the form with following data
| appType | dependents | propertyType | income | otherIncome | livingExpenses | loanRepayments | otherloanRepayments | otherCommitments | totalCClimit |
| Single | 0 | Home | 80000 | 10000 | 500 | 0 | 100 | 0 | 10000 |
User selecting applicant type whether Single/Joint
User selecting number of dependents in household
User selecting to buy Home to live in or Investment property type
User entering his yearly income
User entering other type of income
User entering his/her living expenses
User entering current home loan repayments
User entering any other outstanding loan amounts
User entering any misc commitments
User entering his/her credit card limits
User clicking on the Calculate Loan amount button
Then Anna should see the response returning expected message as "$482,000"
Test validating the amount displayed is what is expected result
